    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Family containing around 50 species of rabbits and hares. They differ from pikas, which also belong to the Lagomorpha order of mammals  in having short furry tails, elongated ears, and and long hind legs adapted for leaping and jumping.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
